  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Photograph</ab>
      <ab type="lido:event" subtype="creation">
        <date>1939</date>
      <persName role="Photographer"><forename>Alija M.</forename><surname>Akšamija</surname><ref type="context" target="info:fedora/context:siba.pn.be7b6d09">Akšamija, Alija M.</ref></persName></ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">A Catholic peasant couple from Sarajevsko polje in <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=B4">Baščaršija</ref> dressed in traditional costume characterized by embroidered white shirts with wide sleeves for both sexes, and unbuttoned, short vests (fermen) with gajtan decorations. The woman’s hair is covered with a tightly fixed headscarf. She is wearing dark dimije and holding her hands folded over her belly, showing a ring on her left index finger. The man has a white <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=C2">čalma</ref> wrapped around his black cap, characteristic for his place of origin. He is in <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=C1">čakšire</ref> with a woven woollen belt (adžem pas) and a <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=B18">bensilah</ref>. The couple stands very close to each other, occupying the right lower quarter of the frame, but they do not touch. There is a street scene in the background and the mountains around Sarajevo on a sunny day are seen behind.</ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet" subtype="comment">The woman is obviously pregnant. Analogue photographic process, negative-positive (Agfa Isopan 17 DIN). Original preserved as a positive on silver bromine paper, stored as a print and a digital record.</ab>
